According to the (self-observed) genealogy report of this fancy AI archetype generator that (supposedly) robs artists of the world in an unethical manner, I am :

22.22% Warrior-Priest Werewolf
11.11% Hedonistic Demon Reincarnate
33.33% War Machine Cover Model
11.11% Techno Bipolar Crybaby
22.22% Undercover Fancypants
00.01% Extraterrestrial Origin

😂😂😂

Now that you’ve had a good giggle, I want to share some bits of my unpredictable life experience that pairs nicely with the somewhat accurate satire above.

I’m in a really unique place in my life right now. Since my mom passed, I’ve been di¢k-deep in grief, knee-deep in growing pains, and occasionally frolicking through the swamps of depression. Despite my ridiculously large box of mental health tools at my disposal, nothing seems to be helping other than this thing I’m writing right now in the moment.

I’ve been reverting to child-like humor that I feel only I would find funny because it’s my way of saying “fu¢k it” in a subtle way instead of blowing everything up in my life like I used to back in my (more) immature days.

(yay for making progress in life)

With that being said, there is a MASSIVE shedding happening. Anyone who’s experienced ego death via psychedelics, a near death experience, or a really bad breakup is more than likely picking up what I’m putting down here.

I’m at this place where I don’t know what to do with my hands and I’m (getting to be) okay with it. Every mask, label, and/or (I)dentity that I once associated with seems less and less appealing and/or important right now.

(hence the satire)

All the above being a roundabout way of reminding myself (and hopefully some others here) to find the small moments to laugh, even if at the expense of your “Self”

…or in this case, your AI-constructed “Selves”

I’m in the great mystery. It’s a beautiful (and wildly chaotic) place to be. I feel well supported by the ones who I go to in my times if need. I appreciate the fu¢k out of you. You know who you are.

***In recent news of @liverking and all the other masked manipulators on this platform, I hope this brought some authenticity into your life.

Bless your beautiful life 🖤

“Am I on the ‘right’ path?”

A question I received last night … so here’s my thoughts on this question 🤓

Let me know your major takeaways and thoughts below 👇

We ALL have “Shadows” AKA the darker, messier parts within us that we might carry shame, embarrassment, guilt, insecurity and/or judgement around.

These are the parts within us that are challenging to acknowledge or that we may have hidden from ourselves and others for a number of reasons - maybe from being told it’s ‘wrong’ or because we carry stories around how we ‘need to’ or ‘should be’ showing up in life…

In this four hour @activateintention experience you’ll be guided through a very intentional journey into your Shadow as you learn to dance with your shadow instead of reject, hide or dismiss it. 

Your Shadow Work Journey includes:

☕️ Opening Circle and Cacao Ceremony to connect in commUNITY

💨 Illuminating the Shadows Breathwork Journey with Nathan

2022 was a fucking GAUNTLET…

So much of a battle that it’s taken me some time to post anything because I’ve spent the last few weeks just doing my best to put myself back together after what seemed like an endless nightmare.

Truthfully, it was the hardest year of my life.

I found myself on multiple occasions feeling broken, confused, depressed, lost, overwhelmed, and downright fucking pissed at the world.

It’s felt like a chore some days to summon the energy to get out of bed and I decided a long time ago that “pushing through the pain” only takes me further away from myself.

I “pushed” through a lot last year - and I refuse to “push” myself in ways that lead me down a path of chaos, despair, or self-destruction.

After dropping $100K on a mastermind, sitting with Ayahuasca and Kambo in the Amazon with my @1nfinitymastermind family, facilitating transformations for hundreds of people, launching the @activateintention podcast with @taylor_wrayyoga while building our community and local events here in Phoenix, spending 66 days in the NICU after Odin came into the world almost 3 months pre-mature, sitting with Bufo (5-MEO) and Huachuma in Idaho, losing my mother in a fatal motorcycle accident unexpectedly, adjusting to newborn dad life, going deeper into my relationship with Jordyn, spending a week in Tulum with @leaderscreateleaders where I was reminded of why I’m here and what my message to the masses is, letting go of my career in fitness after 7 years, and NOW embarking on a new journey with @thespeakerlab to pursue my career as a professional speaker…

You can say last year was A LOT…

A LOT of lessons
A LOT of pain
A LOT of hardship
A LOT of responsibility
A LOT of grief
A LOT of confusion
A LOT of uncertainty
A LOT of faith
A SHIT TON of trust.

ALL OF THAT 👆 has only expanded my capacity to bring in MORE this year…

MORE peace
MORE clarity
MORE grace
MORE certainty
MORE impact
MORE opportunities
MORE pleasure
MORE discernment
MORE choice
MORE love

And I’m here to fuck around and find out MORE.

This is the work. I’m here for it. I’m all the way in.

Are you?

Drop a 💯 in the comments if you’re with me 👇

Anger is a sign of disagreement from within.

In my teens, I was part of gangs, causing harm & ruin. 

Deep down, I disagreed with my actions but didn’t realize the pain I was trying to avoid.

Feeling accepted in the world meant becoming what others wanted…

…but, acceptance begins with Self.

…it took a bullet busting through the back window of the truck and into the dashboard over my shoulder (after an armed robbery) which made me question my choices.

Almost a decade later, I began questioning my perpetual anger.

The discoveries?

① I distrusted everyone (especially me)and I protected myself with anger.

② I assumed the world was against me, a karmic debt for my actions.

③ I chose danger because deep down, I wanted to die.

…and underneath it all was a hurt kid, struggling with BIG emotions that weren’t safe to be seen.

Lessons I’ve learned?

① Be gentle with yourself and others around you.

② Honor the process, no matter how gentle or how intense.

③ Love yourself a little bit more each day.

This journey isn’t about eradicating darkness as much as it is learning how to navigate it.

Every stumble teaches us.

Pain is a very intelligent ally for our awareness.

You’re not defined by your past.

Trust the journey.

Take it one step at a time.

Breathe.

Allow yourself to feel (so that you may heal).

Healing has no deadline or ‘right’ way.

It’s unique to you.

Reach out. Connect. Share your story, struggles, and victories.

You never know who it might inspire.

Your DARKNESS is your DHARMA.

Embrace it, learn from it, and grow alongside of it.

…and always remember:

There’s light on the other side.

You are never alone.

Keep going.

Bless Your Beautiful Life,

~ Nathan ~

You can shoot at all the paper targets.

You can attend all the BJJ classes.

You can attend all the courses and trainings.

You can do everything on paper that looks and sounds good.

…and so on and so forth.

…but if you don’t practice how you play, none of the above matters in REAL LIFE.

Train your mind.
Train your body.
Train your heart.
Train your soul.

For LIFE and DEATH.

…because you will die one day - either by natural causes or external forces.

It’s inevitable.

In this reality, every force has an equal and opposing force.

(Newton’s 3rd Law of Motion)

👇 Which means 👇

The capacity you have to KILL is equal to the capacity you have to CARE.

The capacity you have of LIGHT is equal to the capacity you have of DARK.

The capacity you have to CREATE is equal to the capacity you have to DESTROY.

…and so on and so forth.

The “systems” in our society are designed to domesticate those who participate within them.

The money in your bank account doesn’t mean sh*t when you’re looking down the barrel.

No amount of false validation will supersede the ability to thrive through survival states.

Train your mind.
Train your body.
Train your heart.
Train your soul.

Love is a choice.
Love is unethical.
Love is unapologetic.
Love doesn’t give a sh*t.

Love honors where you are…

…and simultaneously demands the MORE of you.

IS YOUR PERFORMANCE PLATEAUING? READ BELOW 👇

From my beginning in the fitness industry in 2015 to becoming a breathwork guide in 2018, I’ve discovered that breathwork isn’t just a wellness fad. 

It can be a powerful, underutilized tool that can supercharge your performance and help you break through barriers.

But here’s the thing:

The way breathwork is often portrayed in today’s society may be doing more harm than good.

We’re blowing our nervous systems wide open, creating an overload that can leave us feeling frazzled instead of refreshed.

So, what’s the alternative?

Let’s shift the narrative from releasing everything to simultaneously strengthening.

Think of it like this: In treating injuries, do we only focus on relieving the pain?

…or do we also work to fortify and strengthen to prevent future injuries?

Breathwork, when used correctly, does the same for your nervous system and overall performance.

My journey working with athletes like @lanejohnson65 @alex.barrett @kbnelson86 and @prestonmatchett taught me that mastering breathing strategies is a cornerstone of enhancing nervous system health and biomechanical function.

It doesn’t stop at healing or calming—it’s about invoking beneficial stress to amplify performance and force production.

It’s about using breath as a tool, not just for mindfulness or stress release, but for boosting your performance capabilities to the next level.

Remember, breathwork is as multifaceted as you are—it’s here to soothe, empower, and ignite.

Most importantly…it’s the CONTEXT and INTENTION behind your breathwork that ultimately shapes your journey and outcomes.

Feeling stuck in your performance?

Ready to build a stronger, more resilient you?

It’s time to go beyond just healing—it’s time to thrive and excel.

We’ve been lied to our entire lives 👇

Growing up, we were told that darkness was evil (by our parents, religious institutions, etc.), yet they failed to integrate the universal principles of duality, polarity, and unity.

For a long time, I revoked the darkness.

For a long time after, my darkness found ways to express itself in a plethora of ways.

Abuse, manipulation, coercion, and more…

Until I looked at it…

…and once I looked at it, you know what I found?

A really hurt version of me that wanted attention, validation, and LOVE…

…and once I loved that part of me, everything inside of me fell into place.

As Carl G. Jung says,

“Until you make the unconscious conscious, it will direct your life and you will call it fate.”

Think about it this way 👇

The unconscious is the darkness.
The conscious is the light.
The sub-conscious is the in between.

It has NOTHING to do with good and evil.

It has EVERYTHING to do with internal harmony.

Yes, these darker sides can be sinister, but inside that snare lives something sweet.

I recently gave a keynote presentation at @4cornersgathering and I said this exact thing in my speech…

…and so many resonated with it that I HAD to share it.

Drop your thoughts in the comments below 👇

PS : when the final edit is done for my talk, I’ll be posting it on my YouTube.

👇 I’ve been out of integrity with my authenticity 👇

( so I’m owning it here with you all as a witness )

Ever since I fully committed to working in the “healing” field, I've been treading lightly, suppressing myself in the name of sensitivity.

…while unknowingly sacrificing my authenticity.

I preach the power of authenticity, yet I haven’t been FULLY practicing it since I stepped into this space.

Since recently, I have owned this and committed to myself that there will be no more of this.

( this is the main reason @spiritual.psychopath was born )

If anything, my rude awakenings have taught me to be unapologetically myself, no matter what.

So I want to share 5 things with you that I’ve been holding back for the sake of “preserving the peace” here, no matter how confronting they might be👇

1️⃣ I stand by the power and abundance of choice.

Yes, even when the world appears stacked against you. I ache for those genuinely denied freedom, like victims of human trafficking and those living under oppressive regimes.

If someone is not in such extreme circumstances and yet still feels shackled, maybe it's time to examine the chains is all I’m saying.

I've seen people in third-world countries and I personally know so many who have risen from nothing build their own destinies.

So no, I don’t believe that socioeconomic positioning is a life sentence.

2️⃣ Not everyone who is CLAIMING to be a trauma victim is ACTUALLY a REAL VICTIM.

Yes, I said it.

…because trauma is REAL and TRUE victims deserve compassion.

False claims DO exist and it's time we stop turning a blind eye to these endeavors.

3️⃣ Trauma isn't an excuse to wreak havoc on others. 

You've been hurt? I get it. I’ve been hurt too. I’ve been the one to hurt others too. Hurt people hurt people.

We know how this game goes.

…but using that to justify lashing out and then playing the 'narcissist' card on your ex isn't taking responsibility - it's escaping it.

Have you ever let your stories steal your radiance?

For the last several weeks, I’ve been IN IT.

By IN IT, I mean:

• Flooded with anxiousness at the most inconvenient of times (like right before bed)

• Coming into contact with parts of myself I haven’t seen since I was royally screwed over by a former business partner

• Fighting with a demon that lives deeper than the others - this one particularly likes to tell me “I’m worthless” when I’m gaining momentum

It wasn’t until after working with one of my 1:1 clients last week that I reflected on something I said to him.

I said to him,

“Resiliency is hearing the voices in your head that tell you to stop and you choose to keep going, only harder.”

…and the very thing I said to him was the very thing I needed to implement into my life.

(Leaders - IYKYK)

I’ve come into contact with this phenomenon my entire coaching/consulting career over the last 8 years.

…because everything we come into contact with in our reality is either a reflection or a projection.

So you know what I’ve been doing when none of the “tools” seem to be working?

I’ll tell you…

PS : you’ll want to save this post now

I call this the “Ultimate Unf*ckwithable Process” 👇

Simply put, when the invasive thoughts creep in, instead of sitting in them, I move them.

1. I look myself in the mirror (with intensity) and I remind myself who the f*ck I am

EX : I’m the man who fathered 3 amazing children, the man who built 3 companies by 31, and the man who is here to CHANGE 1,000,000 LIVES by 35.

***this isn’t a bullsh*t affirmation - you gotta bring ALL OF YOU here

2. I take 3 BIG BREATHS to FILL UP MY SOUL while in this state

***inhale through the mouth, exhale through the nose x2 then on the 3rd breath, hold at the top and fill yourself up with your FIRE for 5 seconds and let out a SOUND on the exhale

3. I make ONE focused and deliberate action to support it

EX : Send the message I’ve been procrastinating

…easy, right?
